note.div:
In der Tabelle SCHEDULER_SANITY_REFERENCES existieren entsprechende Felder "CATEGORY", "SUBTYPE", "VALUE". Zusätzlich sollte die ID des entsprechenden Job Schedulers angegeben werden, ist sie leer, gelten die Einstellungen für alle Job Scheduler, die diese Datenbank verwenden.
Beispiel für entsprechende INSERT-Statements:
INSERT INTO SCHEDULER_SANITY_REFERENCES ( "SPOOLER_ID", "CATEGORY", "SUBTYPE", "VALUE" ) VALUES ( 'spooler', 'free_memory','jvm', '100000');
INSERT INTO SCHEDULER_SANITY_REFERENCES ( "SPOOLER_ID", "CATEGORY", "SUBTYPE", "VALUE" ) VALUES ( 'spooler', 'disk_space', '/', '2000000' );

The table SCHEDULER_SANITY_REFERENCES has fields named "CATEGORY", "SUBTYPE", "VALUE". There is also a field "ID" which defines the Job Scheduler that the setting applies to. If "ID" is empty, then the setting applies to all Job Schedulers that are using this database.
Example for corresponding INSERT-Statements:
INSERT INTO SCHEDULER_SANITY_REFERENCES ( "SPOOLER_ID", "CATEGORY", "SUBTYPE", "VALUE" ) VALUES ( 'spooler', 'free_memory','jvm', '100000');
INSERT INTO SCHEDULER_SANITY_REFERENCES ( "SPOOLER_ID", "CATEGORY", "SUBTYPE", "VALUE" ) VALUES ( 'spooler', 'disk_space', '/', '2000000' );
